topic.Content:
Chronic diseases include: 
- Cardiovascular diseases, mainly heart disease and chronic respiratory diseases; 
- Stroke; 
- Diabetes; 
- Cancer; 
- Genetic disorders; 
- Others, such as mental disorders, vision and hearing impairment, oral diseases, bone and joint disorders.

The causes (risk factors) of chronic diseases are well established and well known; a small set of common risk factors are responsible for most of the main chronic diseases. These risk factors are modifiable and the same in men and women: 
- Unhealthy diet; 
- Physical inactivity; 
- Tobacco use.
